http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/Noida-police-sends-teams-in-search-of-I-G%E2%80%99s-stolen-car/article14012747.ece

Four teams of the Gautam Budh Nagar Police were on Thursday sent across the country to trace the vehicle of a senior IPS officer, a day after the blue beacon-mounted car was stolen from Noida’s Sector 23.The white SUV was the official car of Anand Swaroop, an Inspector-General with the Indo-Tibetan Border Police (ITBP) posted in Delhi. The car was stolen from outside Mr. Swaroop’s residence in Sector 23 early on Wednesday morning.Given security concerns, the police sounded an alert in the National Capital Region to make sure the vehicle is not misused.“We have sent four teams across the NCR and beyond. The guards in the locality where the car was stolen from have been questioned,” said Senior Superintendent of Police Kiran S.He added that the workers of the place where the car was serviced recently have also been questioned.